<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="357" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,325,605]" pageId="10" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,325,350]" pageId="10" pageNumber="357">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
As in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ale-Rocha, R." box="[355,563,325,350]" pageId="10" pageNumber="357" pagination="17 - 30" refId="ref7071" refString="Ale-Rocha, R. (2006) First description of species of Chvalaea Papp &amp; Foldvari from the Neotropical Region (Diptera, Hybotidae, Ocydromiinae). Zootaxa, 1167, 17 - 30." type="journal article" year="2006">Ale-Rocha (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, plus veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[727,735,340,354]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="357">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[819,827,340,354]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="357">4</subScript>
not reaching the wing margin (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1280,325,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–52" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1529,1551]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,447,1507]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 45–52. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. Wings. 45. Chvalaea amazonica Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 46. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., holotype ♂; 47. Chvalaea boliviana Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 48. Chvalaea catarinensis Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♂; 49. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov., paratype ♂; 50. Chvalaea masneri Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 51. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 52. Chvalaea sinclairi sp. nov., holotype ♂. Abbreviations: bm = basal medial cell; br = basal radial cell; cua = anterior cubital cell; CuA+CuP = anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm = discal medial cell; M 1 = first branch of media; M 4 = fourth branch of media; R 1 = anterior branch of radius; R 2+3 = second branch of radius; R 4+5 = third branch of radius. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612729/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="357">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Hind femur strongly clavate. Fore and mid tarsomeres 3–4 and hind tarsomeres 3–5 ventrally with short, blunt, black spine-like setae (
<figureCitation box="[222,288,400,425]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,914,936]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,185,889]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,185,889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. Fore tarsus. 1. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, blunt, black spine-like ventral setae highlighted; 2. Chvalaea amazonica Ale-Rocha, 2006, absence of black spine-like ventral setae highlighted. Scale bars: Fig. 1 = 0.5 mm; Fig. 2 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612705/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="357">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
